  "body": "```\r\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\n[signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x0 pc=0x5313ae]\r\n\r\ngoroutine 2356 [running]:\r\nmath/big.(*Int).Cmp(0xc02e0ea080, 0x0, 0xffc8aedf61b3f3d2)\r\n    /usr/local/go/src/math/big/int.go:326 +0x2e\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/eth.(*ProtocolManager).synchronise(0xc000238a80, 0xc03b6c31e0)\r\n    /go-ethereum/eth/sync.go:196 +0x182\r\ncreated by github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/eth.(*ProtocolManager).syncer\r\n    /go-ethereum/eth/sync.go:173 +0x313\r\n```\r\n\r\nA clique miner with a fresh database will insta-mine a block, and fast syncing against this state produces a panic. Most probably some TD field is not written out to disk on miner commit causing a sync check against it to go belly up.",
